    "body": "I'm the same problem.\r\n```js\r\n//renderer.js\r\nconst electron = require('electron')\r\nconst BrowserWindow = electron.remote.BrowserWindow\r\n\r\nconst btn = document.getElementById('open')\r\nbtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\r\n    var main = BrowserWindow.getFocusedWindow()\r\n    let newWin = new BrowserWindow({\r\n        frame: true,\r\n        modal: true,\r\n        parent: main\r\n    })\r\n    newWin.on('close', function(){\r\n        newWin = null\r\n    })\r\n    newWin.loadURL('http://localhost/new')\r\n    newWin.show()\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen I close the new window, the main window can not click, can not enter, not even close.\r\n\r\n\r\nElectron version: 1.6.1\r\nOperating system: Windows 10\r\n\r\n"
  },
